steps.description:
If you do not have a good position on your enemy it can cost you your life and can cost your team points and possibly a loss.When moving to a position try to be as inconspicuous as possible. The best positions are usually going to be out in the open where the enemy will not expect you. Most of the time though you can only take one or two shots from out in the open before you are found. Another good position is on the corner a building this will give you cover from enemy fire. Here are the pros and cons of some other positions:
Roof tops while being good for viewing the battle can be detrimental to your ability to snipe. If you must go on a rooftop do not stay long and make sure that if you know you are going to stay for a few shots make sure you stay behind something on the roof and place a CLAYMORE on the top of the ladder so that an enemy soldier that come up the ladder has a nice welcoming present and this will give you time to exit this location. Roof tops are generally safer further away from active areas. Try to choose one where you still have a good view but is away from the main combat areas. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/89/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/8/89/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cranes are extremely effective places to snipe from, as they are high up, and some people falsely believe they are bad, so people don't always look there. They have some cons, as they take time to climb. Claymore the ladders, and check them often. If spotted, jump(don't forget to use your parachute)! {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/25/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/25/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Hill positions can be very effective especially for long range sniping.try to use trees,bushes,rocks and other items in the terrain to mask your position. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9e/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/9e/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet3.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Sniping from vehicles can be done from most transport vehicles where your personal weapon is your defense. Most enemies will not expect a sniper in the back of a Hummer, so if you are in a squad and everyone exits stay in the rear and use it. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8c/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/8/8c/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Short-range sniping shots are best when standing or kneeling in the game because you will need to quickly take the shot and then move because the enemy will probably hear you and then see your position. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c4/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/c4/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet5.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-8Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make sure you take the enemy down with only one bullet. The best way to ensure this is to aim for your enemies forehead or scalp, if you shoot your enemy in either spot you will get a one shot one kill. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0f/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-18.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-18.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/0f/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-18.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-18.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If you cannot get a head shot on your enemy, shoot at whatever part of your enemy is exposed usually one shot from a sniper rifle on the body of most units in the game will cause 3/4 damaged to be assessed to your enemy thus making your second shot very simple and a body shot will assure his demise. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b0/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/b0/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-9Bullet2.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-9Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make sure you can quickly switch to your pistol and use the claymores to defend your position, grenades can be used to allow you to escape a fire fight. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/dc/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-9Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-9Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/d/dc/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-9Bullet3.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-9Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Over 100 meters (328.1 ft) the game tries to calculate for bullet drop. The game does not do an effective job of doing so but you will need to adjust for a slight bit of drop due to enemy movement. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/8c/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/8/8c/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Go into the prone position when setting up for a long range shot. Spend a second or two to settle in. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7c/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/7/7c/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make sure that you watch your enemy for a few seconds to determine his movement patterns. Remember not to take too long, or your target just might disappear behind an obstacle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/67/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/6/67/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Look for the enemies that are lying down or just standing around. Try to avoid moving targets, they are usually more difficult and you may expose your position. However, don't avoid every moving target, otherwise you will never gain valuable experience. In fact, every time you make a successful shot on a moving target, try a little bit harder to find moving targets, eventually you will be good enough to take almost anyone down, moving or not. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b3/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/b3/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet4.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Position the reticle for the long range shot on your enemies head right at the scalp. It will seem like you are adjusting for drop but it is really just because the enemy is so much farther away. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e2/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/e/e2/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet5.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-10Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Know that your pistol,claymore and grenades are your only CQB weapons. Pistol: Aim for the head with your pistol otherwise a decent enemy will finish you off very quickly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/03/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/03/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet1.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Claymores: Place them in areas that are highly-trafficked by the enemy and use them to protect your rooftop positions. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/07/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/07/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet2.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Grenades:Throw grenades to get your enemy to back off of your position or give you enough time to get back to your friendlies. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/80/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/8/80/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet3.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-13Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Essentially, a sniper is useless against enemy armor. So when a tank decides to run you over for laughs, you can't really do much except make the most of your grenades and claymores. This of course, encourages him to shoot you instead. The spotter steps in to assist the sniper in tight fixes. Or at least provide warning when something dangerous is nearby. Special forces: They are possibly the best spotters for infiltration. Cover his back against enemy infantry while he plants the all-important C4 charge. If he knows what he's doing, the enemy can be pinned down for over 5 minutes while you pick off infantry and he sabotages vehicles, artillery, etc. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6d/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/6/6d/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet1.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Assault: Not preferred due to the lack of more effective explosives. Still, they are quite good decoys. Just don't stick to them since they just aren't meant for being willingly trapped behind enemy lines. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/62/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/6/62/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet2.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Support: This is also not preferred. Support units will keep you well stocked on ammo, but they won't be able to do much else. And unlike Assault kits, they have a harder time against medium and heavy vehicles. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9d/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/9d/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet3.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Medic: This is ok, but don't stick to him. He'll provide cover in close quarters and patch you up when you get too injured. Just be sure you take a lot of infantry out, as he can't revive you when someone's guarding your corpse. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/80/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/8/80/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet4.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Sniper: NO. This just increases the number of targets to hit. A good sniper knows that the more spread out they are, the more area their scopes can cover. So two snipers in the same place is useless. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/15/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/1/15/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet5.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Engineer: They usually have big close quarter guns. And they can sabotage vehicles by putting mines right next to their treads. And when you decide to finally escape, get in a vehicle with him. You're more survivable that way. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7c/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet6.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/7/7c/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet6.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Anti-Tank: The second best spotter. Not as efficient in sabotage, but they can save you when confronted with armor. Three cheers for SRAW and ERYX! {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c8/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet7.jpg/v4-460px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet7.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/c8/Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet7.jpg/aid11478-v4-728px-Become-an-Effective-Sniper-in-Battlefield-2-Step-24Bullet7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
